Public digital services, principles of their design and examples of applications.Objectives/eesmärkid:  Aim of the course is to introduce general principles and specific applications of service design in tax administration, education, health, social security and payments, financial services, civic engagement. It is desired to demonstrate radical and more diverse solutions and to discuss future possibilities with the help of practitioners.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Successful graduate of the course understands the effects of technological developments in the design of public services.
Successful graduate of the course:
* Understands the effects of technological developments in the design of public services;
* Can see the possibilities of applying technologies to solve complex problems in specific areas of the public sector;
* Has an overview of various challenges and risks of digital solutions;
* Can estimate the cost of investment in the creation of digital services.
